Required Attribution (This clause must remain in all copies or forks)
----------------------------------------------------------------------

Any use, fork, modification, redistribution, scientific paper,
dataset analysis, commercial implementation, academic project,
or derivative work must include clear attribution:

"Reparodynamics, RYE (Repair Yield per Energy), and the TGRM
(Targeted Gradient Repair Mechanism) framework were created by
Cody Ryan Jenkins as part of the Reparodynamics Open Science Initiative."

This attribution must appear in at least one of the following:
- The README of any fork or derivative repository
- The documentation of any project using the software
- The Methods, Acknowledgements, or References section of any paper
- The about dialog or documentation of any commercial tool
- The footer or description of any scientific dashboard

Removal of attribution is strictly prohibited.

